<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-why-this-recipe"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="why_this_recipe"></span>Why This Recipe<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Creamy and comforting with no cream required</li>



<li>Packed with vegetables in a hidden, kid-friendly way</li>



<li>Easy to prepare with simple, wholesome ingredients</li>
</ul>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredients-you-will-need"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="ingredients_you_will_need"></span>Ingredients You Will Need<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ingredients for cauliflower alfredo on benchtop with text overlay." class="wp-image-28589" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text.jpg" alt="Ingredients for cauliflower alfredo on benchtop with text overlay." class="wp-image-28589" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-ingreds-text-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<div class="wp-block-group ingredient-notes-lt has-theme-palette-7-background-color has-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredient-notes-substitutes-amp-allergy-swaps"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="ingredient_notes_substitutes_allergy_swaps"></span>Ingredient Notes, Substitutes &amp; Allergy Swaps<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Milk</strong>: Use any milk (dairy or plant-based) depending on dietary needs. For an extra decadent version the milk can be swapped for cream. </li>



<li><strong>Parmesan</strong>: Can be swapped for a dairy-free hard cheese alternative if needed.</li>



<li><strong>Panko</strong>: Regular bread crumbs can be used; gluten-free panko works well for coeliac-friendly versions.</li>



<li><strong>Thyme</strong>: Optional, but adds a lovely herbal note to the crumb.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id28535_c6ca4c-78 alignnone ambassador-block-lt wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column28535_805863-98"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-background" id="h-step-by-step-instructions" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="step-by-step_instructions"></span>Step-by-step instructions<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f0f0f0"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<p>Below are illustrated step-by-step instructions to make my <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/condensed-milk-caramel/" title="Condensed Milk Caramel" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="68" data-wpel-link="internal">Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce</a> recipe, if you prefer just the written instructions then head straight to the printable recipe card below.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<p><strong>Step one:</strong> <strong>Prep the Cauliflower and Garlic</strong></p>



<p>Preheat your oven to 160 degrees Celsius (320 F) C (Don’t rush the roasting—low and slow yields the best flavour.)</p>



<p>Let’s get started! Break your cauliflower into florets—not too big, not too small—and scatter them over a baking tray. I like to tear them with my hands for a rustic look (and fewer dishes!). Nestle in your garlic cloves, I tuck them under the florets as they cook a bit faster than the cauliflower. Drizzle everything with olive oil. Spread them out so they roast, not steam.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Cauliflower pieces broken on a lined tray with baking paper on bench top." class="wp-image-28590" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2.jpg" alt="Cauliflower pieces broken on a lined tray with baking paper on bench top." class="wp-image-28590" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-2-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step two:</strong> <strong>Into the Blender They Go</strong></p>



<p>Once the cauliflower is soft and lightly golden, remove about three-quarters of it (plus all the garlic) and transfer them into a blender or food processor. Keep the rest on the tray—we’re going to crisp that up later for the topping.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Glass bowl with cooked slightly roasted cauliflower." class="wp-image-28600" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12.jpg" alt="Glass bowl with cooked slightly roasted cauliflower." class="wp-image-28600" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-12-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Optional Topping</strong></p>



<p>Increase the temperature of your oven to 200 degrees celsius (400 F) and bake the remaining cauliflower for for a further 5-10 minutes or until brown and crispy.</p>



<p>Cook your pasta in boiling salted water as per the packet instructions. When cooked remember to reserve around 1 cup of the pasta cooking water before draining.</p>
</div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div>

</div></div>    <div class="dpsp-email-save-this-tool " style="background-color: #f2e2d3;">        <div class="hubbub-save-this-form-wrapper"><h3 class="hubbub-save-this-heading">Save This Recipe!</h3><div class="hubbub-save-this-message"><p>I'll email this post to you, so you can easily come back to it later!</p></div><div class="hubbub-save-this-form-only-wrapper"><form name="hubbub-save-this-form" method="post" action="">                    <input type="text" name="hubbub-save-this-snare" class="hubbub-save-this-snare hubbub-block-save-this-snare" /><p class="hubbub-save-this-emailaddress-paragraph-wrapper"><input aria-label="Email Address" type="email" placeholder="Email Address" name="hubbub-save-this-emailaddress" value="" class="hubbub-block-save-this-text-control hubbub-save-this-emailaddress" required /></p><p class="hubbub-save-this-submit-button-paragraph-wrapper"><input type="submit" style="" value="Save This Recipe " class="hubbub-block-save-this-submit-button" name="hubbub-block-save-this-submit-button" /></p><input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-postid" class="hubbub-save-this-postid" value="28535" />                    <input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-posturl" class="hubbub-save-this-posturl" value="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce/" />                    <input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-posttitle" class="hubbub-save-this-posttitle" value="Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce" />                    <input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-success-redirect-url" class="hubbub-save-this-success-redirect-url" value="" /></form>            </div></div>    </div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id28535_db0808-b5 alignnone ambassador-block-lt wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column28535_7d1b42-14"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f0f0f0"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group has-background" style="background-color:#f0f4f4"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<p><strong>Step three: Add the Good Stuff</strong></p>



<p>Now comes the magic. Add your grated parmesan cheese and milk to the blender with the cauliflower and garlic. This is where everything starts coming together into a rich and creamy sauce that smells amazing.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p><em>I use full-fat milk for extra creaminess, but any milk you like will work here.</em></p>
</blockquote>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Roasted Garlic, parmesan cheese and milk in a food processor on benchtop." class="wp-image-28591" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3.jpg" alt="Roasted Garlic, parmesan cheese and milk in a food processor on benchtop." class="wp-image-28591" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-3-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Sep four:.&nbsp;Blend Until Dreamy</strong></p>



<p>Blitz it all up! You’re aiming for a silky smooth texture—thick and creamy like a classic Alfredo. You might need to stop and scrape down the sides once or twice. It should hold its shape on a spatula but still glide off easily.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p><em>If it feels too thick, don’t worry—we’ll use a little pasta water later to loosen it.</em></p>
</blockquote>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Spatula held up with thick creamy cauliflower alfredo sauce on it, blender with sauce in background below." class="wp-image-28593" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5.jpg" alt="Spatula held up with thick creamy cauliflower alfredo sauce on it, blender with sauce in background below." class="wp-image-28593" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-5-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<p><strong>Step five: Toss It All Together</strong></p>



<p>Time to bring it all home. Cook your pasta until al dente, then drain (don’t forget to save some of that pasta water!). Pour the sauce over the hot pasta in a big pot or Dutch oven, and use tongs to mix it all together gently.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p><em>This is when it turns from “just cauliflower” into pure creamy comfort.</em></p>
</blockquote>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Cauliflower alfredo sauce poured on top of cooked pasta in ceramic dutch oven, hand holding tongs to mix." class="wp-image-28601" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13.jpg" alt="Cauliflower alfredo sauce poured on top of cooked pasta in ceramic dutch oven, hand holding tongs to mix." class="wp-image-28601" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-13-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Cauliflower alfredo sauce mixed through cooked pasta topped with chopped parsley in a ceramic dutch oven pan on benchtop." class="wp-image-28595" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7.jpg" /><noscript><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7.jpg" alt="Cauliflower alfredo sauce mixed through cooked pasta topped with chopped parsley in a ceramic dutch oven pan on benchtop." class="wp-image-28595" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-300x300.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-150x150.jpg 150w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-768x768.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-600x600.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-500x500.jpg 500w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-720x720.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-360x360.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-180x180.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-7-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
