<div class="wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-1 one-column"><div class="gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column">
<div class="wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column tips gb-block-layout-column"><div class="gb-block-layout-column-inner">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-top-tips"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="top_tips"></span>Top Tips<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>Here is how you can make these Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce perfectly every time!</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Try not to be tempted to roast the cauliflower hot and fast, it does much better in a moderate oven for a little longer.&nbsp;</li>



<li>For a protein boost, serve with grilled or <a href="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/poached-chicken-breast/" data-wpel-link="internal">poached chicken</a>, <a href="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/pan-fried-fish/" data-wpel-link="internal">pan fried fish</a> or stir in cooked white beans.</li>



<li>This sauce freezes well—great for batch cooking.</li>



<li>Fettuccine, penne, or shells hold the sauce beautifully.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Cauliflower alfredo sauce mixed through cooked pasta topped with crispy roasted cauliflower, panko bread crumbs, thyme, parsley and parmesan cheese in a ceramic dutch oven pan on benchtop with green and white checkered tea towel." class="wp-image-28596" data-lazy-srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-150x100.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8.jpg" alt="Cauliflower alfredo sauce mixed through cooked pasta topped with crispy roasted cauliflower, panko bread crumbs, thyme, parsley and parmesan cheese in a ceramic dutch oven pan on benchtop with green and white checkered tea towel." class="wp-image-28596" srcset="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8.jpg 1200w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-720x480.jpg 720w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-360x240.jpg 360w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-180x120.jpg 180w, https://mykidslickthebowl.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/cauliflower-alfredo-sauce-8-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



