<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column28535_3d09fb-b3"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-this-recipe-suitable-for-baby-led-weaning"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="how_to_make_this_recipe_suitable_for_baby_led_weaning"></span>How to Make This Recipe Suitable For Baby Led Weaning<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Don't season the cauliflower alfredo sauce with salt before portioning your babies serve.</li>



<li>Serve sauce over soft pasta shapes like penne or large spirals that baby can grasp.</li>



<li>Skip the  crumb topping for young babies just starting their <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://mykidslickthebowl.com/sign-up/" title="My Kids Lick The Bowl Email Preferences" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="66" data-wpel-link="internal">baby led weaning</a> journey</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

</div></div>

